  "definition": "**Tidal Volume (TV or VT)** is the volume of air moved in or out of the lungs during a single normal breath. It represents the difference between the volume of air in the lungs at the end of inspiration and at the end of expiration during quiet breathing.",
  "clinical_relevance": [
    "Used to calculate **minute ventilation** (MV = TV × respiratory rate)",
    "Critical for **mechanical ventilation** settings",
    "Low tidal volume ventilation (6-8 mL/kg IBW) reduces ventilator-induced lung injury",
    "Decreased in restrictive lung diseases",
    "May be normal or increased in obstructive lung diseases"
  ],
